1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,120
Well, I’m in a relationship now.

2
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:03,720
<i>I figured it out now.</i>

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:04,680
It’s Gam.

4
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:05,720
<i>Don’t break up with her.</i>

5
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,720
<i>I believe that we can both work as a group</i>

6
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,000
<i>and like someone at the same time</i>

7
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:14,000
<i>because both are part of our lives.</i>

8
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,720
<i>Since we have time,</i>
<i>we should have watched the movie.</i>

9
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,880
Can we watch it next week?

10
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:23,360
Let’s not keep a five-meter distance

11
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:27,160
because even five centimeters
feels too far apart.

12
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,720
LOVE YOU TO DEBT
LIFE, ROMANTIC / 135 MINUTES

13
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:38,880
THAME AND DYLAN SONG DISCUSSION
6 P.M. - 10 P.M.

14
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,040
THAME AND PEPPER DISCUSSION 6 P.M.
THAME RECORDS THE DEMO 7 P.M. - 8.30 P.M.

15
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,200
DRAFT THE MV REF 9.00 P.M. - 11.00 P.M.

16
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:51,880
What’s wrong?

17
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:53,440
Per,

18
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,880
help me.

19
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:58,400
So, you haven't watched the movie
with him yet?

20
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,480
Uh-huh.

21
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,760
Lucky enough, you’ve met someone
who understands you.

22
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,560
All right. I’ll help.

23
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:16,600
How about we move this to that day?

24
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,760
We must work hard all day one day.

25
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,680
Are you okay with that? See?

26
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:23,760
You can save this date
and go to the movies with him.

27
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:26,440
All right. I’ll call and ask him now.

28
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,960
Thame!

29
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,760
Let’s finalize the new single already.

30
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,400
So, will a breakdance be included?

31
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,040
You must decide as soon as possible.

32
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,680
The work scale is different, you know.

33
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:39,280
- I must quickly plan the work.
- Thame.

34
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:41,120
I can’t decide
until I get to listen to both versions.

35
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,280
Record a guide demo for me, okay?

36
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,840
You can use the old lyrics.

37
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,800
Hey, it looks like
we’ve got a free day, right?

38
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,240
I’ll book that day then.

39
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:52,120
THAME - DYLAND RECORD THE SONG

40
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,720
So we can wrap it up quickly.

41
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,960
I’ll put mine here.

42
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:59,400
FINALIZE THE DANCE WITH THAME

43
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,120
THAME

44
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,880
Hello?

45
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,360
<i>Po,</i>

46
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,640
<i>I’m sorry.</i>

47
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,120
I still can’t make time for our movie day.

48
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,800
But if there’s a day
I finish my work quickly,

49
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,400
I’ll call you right away.

50
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,880
It might be a bit abrupt.

51
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,400
<i>I really can’t promise when.</i>

52
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,960
It’s all right. I understand.

53
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,000
<i>I’ve been really busy these days.</i>

54
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:15,880
But Per told me that

55
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,080
when he’s busy,

56
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,480
he will send Gam photos
to let her know what he’s doing.

57
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,400
Are you okay with that?

58
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,040
Yeah.

59
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,640
Okay.

60
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,160
But if you’re not familiar
with doing that,

61
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,960
don’t worry at all.

62
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,520
I can handle it just fine.

63
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:43,400
And you’re not even going to ask me

64
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,640
if I can handle it just fine too?

65
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,080
Anyway,

66
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,800
I’ll make time to watch
the movie with you.

67
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,720
I promise.

68
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,080
Yeah.

69
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:04,160
I’ll wait.

70
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,160
Sure.

71
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,800
Let’s stock up on a bunch of stuff, okay?

72
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,960
For late-night snacks and all that.

73
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:10,680
It looks like we have to work
all day and night.

74
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,680
Yeah. That sounds like a good idea.

75
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,320
I think we should stock up
on lots of ready-to-eat food

76
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,640
because someone who loves ordering food

77
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,760
is never around
when it’s time to work together.

78
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,120
Eh?

79
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,320
That’s because you guys split up and work.

80
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,440
I’m on my own.

81
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,400
How can I be with you all everywhere, huh?

82
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:40,120
So, we’re going to be busy
both day and night, right?

83
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,040
Of course.

84
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,080
Otherwise, we won’t be left
with any time to work on the MV.

85
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,480
Hey, but…

86
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:51,680
I think we can start working
on our MV now.

87
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,600
But we need someone to help you, Thame.

88
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,000
I’m not available.

89
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,040
I’m not talking about you.

90
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,680
I’m talking about Po.

91
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,640
I think he can help us.

92
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,560
That makes sense.

93
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,120
- He’s a director.
- Yeah.

94
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,680
I agree with that,

95
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,560
so our secret about making music
won’t get leaked.

96
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,800
Well done, bro.

97
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,800
How about his own work?

98
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,400
It seems he’s busy too.

99
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,760
Come to think of it, you’ve already got
a lot of work too, buddy.

100
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,440
Let’s put it this way then.

101
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,640
I’ll take care of the MV.

102
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,520
You’re acting strange, Jun.

103
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,680
Eh?

104
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,000
I’m just trying to help out.

105
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,320
Why are you so suspicious?

106
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,320
So, it’s settled now.

107
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,640
I’ll get going.

108
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,560
Hey, hold on. What about the welfare work?

109
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,720
Eh?

110
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,160
You all can help each other
with that, okay?

111
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,640
Bye-bye.

112
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,000
This way, it plays right into his hands

113
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,160
getting someone else
to do the work for him.

114
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,960
I bet he’ll just lie down and relax.

115
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,200
True.

116
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,520
I think I started to feel sorry
for Po a bit.

117
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,960
Per, why did you mention that?

118
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,200
Look.

119
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,120
I’m sure Jun is going
to give Po more trouble.

120
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:13,400
You… really can’t figure it out?

121
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,880
I said that

122
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,000
not because I wanted him to work
on it or anything,

123
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,800
I’m just trying to come up with an excuse,

124
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,840
so that he can come and stay close to you.

125
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,640
You can just work on the MV

126
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:33,640
and let him sit there and do nothing.

127
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,280
Shit.

128
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,080
That’s your plan?

129
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,800
Of course.

130
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:42,840
Now look at Jun,

131
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,280
taking the chance to slip away already.

132
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,240
Per,

133
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,120
this is your favorite, isn’t it?

134
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:51,840
Do you want it?

135
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:53,960
You did great, buddy.

136
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:57,120
But you’re totally not keeping up
with Jun, man!

137
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:07,400
THAMETEEMA: I WENT TO THE SUPERMARKET

138
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,040
Are you smiling at me?

139
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,000
Hey.

140
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,200
Who would smile at someone like you?

141
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,600
I smiled because…

142
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,080
You're missing Thame, aren’t you?

143
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,280
Can’t I?

144
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,400
It looks like you’ve gone too far, huh?

145
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:29,400
Anyway, if you miss him that much,

146
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,400
are you interested in working
close to him?

147
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:33,520
What do you mean?

148
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,640
I’m now in charge of the MV thing.

149
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,039
Do you want to help me,

150
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:42,400
so you’ll be hanging around that area?

151
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,440
Are you serious, Jun?

152
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,880
But I have a condition.

153
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:51,640
You must really help me ideate
and work on it.

154
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,800
Well,

155
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,440
but I’m not that good at it.

156
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:01,240
Also, this is important work, isn’t it?

157
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,560
So? Does that mean
you don’t want to stay close to Thame?

158
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:07,160
I want to,

159
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,200
but do you think it’s a good idea

160
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,960
to let me do such important work?

161
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,400
So, you don’t want to be close to Thame?

162
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,960
That’s not what I mean!

163
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,120
But…

164
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,680
- I mean….
- Ugh. You’re annoying me.

165
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,440
Don’t take too long
to make a decision, okay?

166
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,240
The chance is right in front of you,
so, will you take it or not?

167
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,800
Why do you have to use Thame as bait?

168
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,360
And is it working, huh?

169
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,640
Fine.

170
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,800
I’ll help.

171
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,880
Deal.

172
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,200
It’s settled, then.

173
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,560
I’ll send you references.

174
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,880
Work hard, okay?

175
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:50,000
If you don’t do it well
and it’s not impressive,

176
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,640
Thame will certainly be mad at you.

177
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,000
You silly!

178
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,760
Don’t you think I have
my own work to handle too, huh?

179
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:58,440
What work?

180
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,360
You don’t usually work.

181
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,840
I’ve never seen you work.

182
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,640
<i>This is the first draft</i>
<i>of the documentary.</i>

183
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,080
<i>Add the subtitles for me.</i>

184
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,440
<i>The deadline is the day after tomorrow.</i>

185
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,520
Shit.

186
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,000
Why did he assign me the work
at this hour?

187
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,560
THAME

188
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,360
Hello?

189
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,560
Are you busy now?

190
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,720
<i>We can talk.</i>

191
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,640
Jun already told you to help
with the MV, right?

192
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,600
<i>Yeah.</i>

193
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,080
Don’t worry.

194
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,680
I’ll give it my all.

195
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,280
This won’t make things harder
for you, right?

196
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,720
<i>It won’t.</i>

197
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,720
<i>I won’t disappoint you.</i>

198
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,720
I’m now preparing some references
to discuss with you tomorrow too.

199
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,400
When are you coming?

200
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,120
After work.

201
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,720
<i>I think it’s around 6 p.m.</i>

202
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:09,840
Okay.

203
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,760
I’ll wait to discuss it with you.

204
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,280
Yeah.

205
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:19,160
Today, I sent you five photos,

206
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:23,240
but you only sent me four.

207
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,360
Huh?

208
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,240
That’s it for now.

209
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,320
I’ll hang up.

210
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,720
Then roll.

211
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,720
- And then…
- That works. Hey, yo!

212
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,960
- Yo!
- Po!

213
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:09,880
Whoa.

214
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:13,120
It took you ages. Come now.

215
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,320
Let's see what work
you've gotten done today.

216
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,600
That’s strange. That’s super strange.

217
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,360
What?

218
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,160
What are these references?

219
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,200
Do you really understand MARS?

220
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,920
A cutting-edge concept is good,
but is this MARS’ identity?

221
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:52,200
Also, you said you'd finish work
by 6 p.m., but why are you so late?

222
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,120
The traffic was heavy, okay?

223
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,640
Do you know the phrase "buffer time"?

224
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:03,720
I can't deal with this.

225
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,560
Earlier this afternoon,

226
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:09,040
I still saw Jun sitting there
looking for lots of references.

227
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:11,520
Now, look at him, checking on the work
in such a serious mode.

228
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,680
It seems like he’s trying
to mess with you.

229
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,240
He never stops his bad behaviors.

230
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,920
Back when I started to get close
with Thame,

231
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,160
he used to do the same thing.

232
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,080
Eh? Aren’t you listening to the music?

233
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,840
I’m just wearing them.

234
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:30,800
When it's something I don't care about,
I pretend I didn't hear it.

235
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,240
Wow,

236
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:35,160
the secret of the mysterious land
of the sky dragon

237
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:37,200
has been revealed, everyone!

238
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:40,120
So, does that mean you've heard
everything over all these years?

239
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:50,680
You should brief them with the song.

240
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,040
The song and the MV
have to be done together anyway.

241
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:55,840
Go already.

242
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,080
This is so outdated.

243
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,200
Look at what you’ve done.

244
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,080
I came to brief about the song.

245
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:13,400
Yeah.

246
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,720
Go ahead.

247
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:16,800
You don’t need to do that.

248
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,480
I briefed him yesterday.

249
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,480
It’s my work, so I can handle it myself.

250
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:23,840
You’re busy, aren’t you?

251
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,120
Go do your work.

252
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,360
Go.

253
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:30,240
- Go.
- Jun!

254
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,640
But I want to brief you on it
by myself anyway.

255
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,200
It’s my work.

256
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:44,320
Are you going to brief us?
Brief me on it then.

257
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,480
Will you?

258
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,800
You and me. Let’s go.

259
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:47,800
Let’s do it now.

260
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,600
What’s your brief?

261
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,520
Come here.

262
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,240
You're such a liar!

263
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,160
You said you’d have me do the work
so I could stay with Thame,

