everyone still wants to be MARS.

529
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:40,720
And I want to prove to you
that we can do it.

530
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:45,160
Also, we don’t need to leave anyone behind

531
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:47,640
just to become successful.

532
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,400
Fine.

533
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:58,640
Now tell me how you define success.

534
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,920
Total sales?

535
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,240
Engagement?

536
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,600
BA jobs?

537
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,680
If not, then what is it?

538
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:16,600
It's about how the TPOP world is going
to be the new wave in the music industry.

539
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,800
Do you think the reason
I separated you from the group

540
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:24,360
is because the market wants you?

541
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:27,320
The reason I separated you is

542
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:31,520
because you’re the one who can take
TPOP beyond just the local scene.

543
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,360
You’re the one chosen by Korea,

544
00:36:34,720 --> 00:36:38,920
so this is an opportunity to make
people pay attention to TPOP.

545
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:42,600
The value you're creating
isn’t just money.

546
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,840
You’re building the music industry.

547
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,160
What you're doing right now

548
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:50,000
is causing the company
to miss out on a huge opportunity.

549
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:54,480
Really?

550
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,240
You know me well, Thame.

551
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:00,480
I love this industry
more than anyone else,

552
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:03,160
and I always look ahead,
focusing on the bigger picture.

553
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:08,520
What if my bigger picture
doesn't just include me?

554
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,320
You told me yourself that

555
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:15,440
what you want most
is the opportunity for TPOP.

556
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:21,200
And I believe it's not just me
who can make it happen.

557
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:25,440
MARS as a group can do it too.

558
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:26,960
What do you say?

559
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,920
But they only want you.

560
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,560
The contract only involves you.

561
00:37:33,640 --> 00:37:35,520
That’s because, in the past,
you've only focused the spotlight on me.

562
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:38,680
But this time,

563
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:41,200
if I broaden that spotlight,

564
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:44,480
making every member shine and stand out,

565
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,520
do you think we stand a chance?

566
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:54,080
If you want the world
to pay attention to TPOP,

567
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:59,040
a group can get more attention
than just a solo artist.

568
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:15,360
Fine.

569
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:16,880
Tell me your plan, then.

570
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:21,160
I'll create a new song under MARS.

571
00:38:22,120 --> 00:38:24,400
If my song beats Ice's song

572
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:26,000
and tops every chart,

573
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:28,880
then we'll all get to go there.

574
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:35,760
What if you fail?

575
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:39,440
You'll go back to fulfilling
the original contract, right?

576
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:44,320
Yes. I’ll do that.

577
00:38:45,120 --> 00:38:49,760
But you know that Oner will not help you
with anything, right?

578
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,440
Just don’t get in a way.

579
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:12,200
Per, I’ve already talked to the company.

580
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:13,520
I need your help.

581
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:30,480
LOVE YOU TO DEBT

582
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:43,640
<i>If you’re still waiting at the cinema,</i>
<i>just don’t wait anymore.</i>

583
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,400
<i>I think he already forgot</i>
<i>about his date with you.</i>

584
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:48,680
<i>Something happened.</i>

585
00:39:58,240 --> 00:40:00,200
<i>Would you mind if I ask you out?</i>

586
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:02,680
<i>Will you doubt me if I say I like you?</i>

587
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,560
<i>If your heart’s not taken, it’s true</i>

588
00:40:06,080 --> 00:40:08,320
<i>Head home. Don’t wait anymore.</i>

589
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,080
You aren’t going to watch it anymore?

590
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:47,760
I’m sorry I’m late.

591
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:01,600
Did I make it in time?

592
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,600
I thought you were busy with the song.

593
00:41:06,480 --> 00:41:07,360
I was.

594
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:09,720
But why…

595
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:14,960
But you are important, too.

596
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,880
I don’t want to break our promise anymore.

597
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:05,000
MAKE A SONG

598
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:06,360
Does anyone have any ideas?

599
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:09,440
I do. I want to make a love song.

600
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:11,760
What kind of love
do you want the song to be about?

601
00:42:11,840 --> 00:42:14,480
Are you looking for song ideas
or trouble with me?

602
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:18,000
What did you fight with Jun about?
Nothing serious, right?

603
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:19,880
It is, actually.

604
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:23,280
Why are you avoiding me?
Can’t we just talk it out?

605
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,920
Why do I have to play
this stupid game with you?

606
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:27,240
Because it's going to be a long talk.

607
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,120
About both the song and Po.
